76561198024239094,Recommended,489600,30268297,Posted: 1 March,all,Keen.J,"I play a bit of golf in my spare time and thought I would purchase this game as a way to still play a round or two when the British weather is not so good, which it is a lot of the time.What I didn't bank on was that this game so accurately depicts your swing that it can be used as a training aid for the real game.My real game isn't the greatest, in fact I cannot use drivers or woods because I always hook or slice the ball quite badly. Using the shot analysis in game, I found that my back swing and transition into the forward swing was much too fast and I was losing the club quite a lot resulting in my hooks and slices.I slowed down my back swing considerably and BINGO, I was hitting those drivers down the middle of the fairway.Now, I havn't has a chance to practice the slower backswing on a real golf course yet but when I do I will let you know if it has solved my problem."
76561198067323734,Recommended,489600,28269718,"Posted: 9 December, 2016",all,davideliasirwin,"Oculus Rift Review:Pros:- The closest thing to real golf that I have ever experienced in a video game.- Interface is smart and unobtrusive.  Pull the course map out of your back pocket, look at your wrist to see distance to hole, elevation change, wind direction.- Simulation feel:  Feels like the PC version of The Golf Club only now in virtual reality.  My first couple holes I was swinging very hard and robotic( a problem I have in real life golf) and my shots were all over the place.  Once I slowed down my tempo and started a relax swing I started getting closer to par.- Sinking a ten foot put in the game is just as satisfying as in real life.-  Really fun to play if you like real life golf.Cons:- performance is a little bad on a 970, but there are so many technologies implemented and cross talking that I am not sure who to blame.  It is hard to judge how all the different technologies will work together, between OculusSDK, ASW, ATW, OpenVR, SteamVR, SteamVR reprojection there are bound to be some issues.  It is playable but it gets a little choppy.- a few minor bugs:  Sometimes the drop zone is too close to the water.  Sometimes the ball is too close to an obstruction to get a swing off(might be user error).  The map bugged after the 6 hole, every hole after that only showed the 6th hole map.- Controls work pretty well but could use some optimization for the rift.  Specifically the button that selects.  In the rift the capacitive button that is mapped to ""select"" picks up a button touch when it should probably only pick up a button push.Overall:If you have a Rift of Vive and like golf, this is a must buy."
