,Recommended,489600,26122119,"Posted: 19 October, 2016",all,Paul,"This is good implementation of golf in VR. The tutorial gets you off to a good start and the controls are intuitive.Your golf bag is standing just in front of you and you hover your hand over the clubs to make your selection. Initially, the yardage for a club is blank, but once the game knows how far you personally hit that club, it's remembered for next time. One thing I might like to see added in this aspect of the game is the ability to choose to toggle holding the club or map as opposed to having to hold the trigger the whole time.The map in your back pocket is good for seeing the overall hole and checking distances (the dots are 50 yards apart as a guide). Your watch has handy info, too. Haptic feedback is well-done; you know if you're in the right spot to grab your map and you can feel the ground with the clubhead before you swing.The teleporting system is nice. You can zip straight to a stance in front of your ball, or choose to walk along the course and take in the scenery. Reviewing your swing in 3D afterwards is pretty cool. It's like it draws your swing with TiltBrush and you can see how smooth you were and how far back the backswing was.The graphics look great even on low settings, IMO. I get better performance from this game on higher settings than I do in Pool Nation VR, for example. The golf glove texture on the Vive controller is a nice touch. Recommended."
