,Recommended,489600,26135081,"Posted: 20 October, 2016",all,Rafport,"A great and very challenging golf simulator, this is intended to be simulative so forget to stay into the par easily, not for casual players. I'm extremely curious to see further additions, but even now (very first early access with 4 courses locked) there are plenty of holes.Many users complains about performances, surely the game need optimizations, but I'm playing with a 970 and it's acceptable with graphics on mid (low and mid on my system runs almost the same). This game absolutely need an in game supersampling slider, it's very aliased on trees (and with antialiasing very blurry on everything distant).I could write more on what could be added or polished, but the truth is than even now Golf Club crush any other golf game for VR. If you're interested in this sport, it's the game to buy."
,Recommended,489600,31937277,Posted: 24 May,all,(N$A) DOC_5150,"This game truly captures EVERYTHING the game of golf has to offer! I LOVE golf and if you do too this is a must have for VR.PROS:* The ball tracker. swing tracker and the physics are spot on.* The sounds and realistic graphics create an ambiance of being on a golf course.* There are a myriad of settings that a VR golf game should have (i.e. shaft stiffness, club length, putter weight, and even a clubface offset adjuster to square the clubface if you attach the controller to a device)* You can pickup, throw and hit damn near anything in the game (i.e. tee box blocks, yardage signs, flagsticks, your clubs and even your entire bag). If there are clubs in the bag when you pick it up they will fly out of the bag the way they would if it was real life.CONS:* Hard to swing with the Touch controllers, but that's not the game developers fault. I'm working on adding a club shaft extension to the controller.* No multiplayer or tournam3ents, but it looks like that will be implemented soon."
