76561198041226378,Not Recommended,489600,28891803,"Posted: 31 December, 2016",all,urthpainter,"I had a lot of fun with this game in early access, and hoped for improvement.  unfortunately...In the most recent version of the game, I frequently get a studder on my club animation while swinging which radically effects the resulting shot - most noticable on finesse chips and putts that will be (again radically) short or long.  With my competative mind set, I feel cheated every time this happens, and makes it very difficult to finish rounds without quitting the game in disgust.  Worth noting I've tried some changes with my VR setup for better results, nothing yet.  Other VR games are running flawlessly.edit: In earlier versions of the game I occasionally ran into this performance issue, but now it happens multiple times per round.  The effect on putts and chips makes this game umplayable for me.Golf Grades (again - my experience - it seems like different people really have different experiences with the motion tracking and club success in this game).Driver:  F- , Yes, F minus - Driver to me is one of the easiest shots in golf (real golf).  not THE easiest, but one of.  It is a single repeatable swing, with a huge faced club, on a ball teed way up.  For the life of my, I can't hit driver in this game.  Half the time I see the club head go right through the ball, the other half I get wildly inconsistent results.  It is a worthless club to me in this game.  I use 3I as my driving club.  How in the world can 3i be so easy to hit off the tee an driver is not?Fairway Woods:  F   I can hit these just slightly better than driver, and so?  though I've tried, and tried, and tried... again, not useful clubs for me to use.Irons:  C   For me, a full swing iron can end up 30 yards short, 20 yards long, sometimes correct... but I have no idea why shots are ending up where they do after 100's (probably 1000's) of swings.Chipping:  D   Ultimatly I ask, does this game provide the finesse around the green with wedges that the pros play with?  The answer is a resounding: NO!  Not even close - and the greens in this game require incredible finesse in order to score.  Chipping (in this game) has this kind of robotic land and predictable release that is unnatural.  Combine this with percentage ranges based on bad lies (like a 60-80% contact in deep rough)?  The result of a chip may have very little to do with your skill, and more to do with a lucky (or unlucky) contact%, and an unnatural rollout.  Can a good chip be hit?  Yes, especially with a good lie - and with the short roll out you always have a chance for a chip to roll in the hole (if your on the correct line).  But I would Way rather have more control of spin options, so that with practice I could roll out, stop the ball, or backspin.  This is the type of control needed to score on some of the very challenging greens in this game.  Chipping has been further harmed (for me) with occasional chips that go way further or way shorter than expected.Putting:  A, when it works.   Occasional random results can have a short putt getting bashed through the hole and 10+ feet on your next putt...  this type of result in a golf game is beyond frustrating - its a game killer.  I feel the hole edge is a bit unforgiving (you really have to get a lot of the hole, and at correct speed to make putts), and putting certain hole locations on fast greens can be unfair (3 and 4 putts with good attepts is not uncommon).Video Game GradesGraphics  C  - while it is impressive how the entire golf course is there in real time, the actual visuals are average.Sound C  - I feel sound could have been a real benefit to this game in terms of building the environment and letting the player know about wind/ wind direction.  Sound is very average, and really adds very little to the overall presentation beyond the necessary swing noises and such.Control  D  -   I'm running into a lot of issues, and have to mark this down accordingly.Fun Factor  F  - Until I can play a clean game with consistency - playing this game is more a test of patience than fun.edit:  my review has done a 180 since early access - because it plays a worse game of golf than it did in earlier versions.  Clubs like driver and fairway woods did not improve in how they are balanced.  My consistency with irons, wedges and putter have gotten worse with extended play.  This is not a ringing endorcement for a game where you  want the ability to find a groove and have fun playing golf.  This final version for me is a disappointment"
